com.ibm.team.repository.common
Interface IChangeEvent

All Superinterfaces:
IChangeEventHandle, IItem, IItemHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle, ISimpleItem, ISimpleItemHandle
public interface IChangeEvent
extends ISimpleItem, IChangeEventHandle

Represents a modification to the repository. The repository records an event for each modification made to it, and associates that event with the repository object modified.

Since:
0.5

getTime

java.sql.Timestamp getTime()
Returns the date/time associated with this repository modification.

Returns:
The date/time associated with this repository modification. If this item was retrieved from the repository, it will never be null. If non-null, the value will be that as set by setTime(Timestamp) (if non-null), or the repository time at the time this item was created.

setTime

Sets the date/time associated with this repository modification.

Parameters:
time - The date/time associated with this repository modification. May be null. If null and this item is saved, then the value set will be that of the current system time of the repository to which it's saved.

getContributors

java.util.List getContributors()
Returns the list of contributors that participated in the creation of this event. Typically the author (getAuthor()) is not included in this value, but the exact definition of this field value is per the component package that created it. The order of the contributors in the list represents the order of the contributors as they were initially saved.

Returns:
An unmodifiable list of IContributorHandle contributors that participated in the creation of this event. Never null.

setContributors

void setContributors(java.util.List contributors)
Sets the list of contributors that participated in the creation of this event. Typically the author (getAuthor()) is not included in this value, but the exact definition of this field value is per the component package that created it. The order of the contributors in the list represents the order of the contributors as they will be saved (and the order that will be present in subsequent requests to getContributors()).

Parameters:
contributors - A collection of IContributorHandle contributors that participated in the creation of this event. The list of contributors replaces any contributors that may have been set on this instance. May be null. If null, the list of contributors on this instance is cleared. The list is not modified.

getProcessArea

IAuditableHandle getProcessArea()
Returns a reference to the process area that this ChangeEvent is associated to. While the signature of this method types an IAuditableHandle, the actual type of handle returned will be that of the process area that is associated to this event.

Returns:
A handle to the process area that this ChangeEvent is associated to. Will be null if this event has no such association.

setProcessArea

void setProcessArea(IAuditableHandle processArea)
Sets the process area to be associated to this event.

Parameters:
processArea - A handle to a process area. May be null. There is no verification, either client or server-side, that the referenced auditable handle refers to a process area handle type.

setStringExtension

void setStringExtension(java.lang.String key,
                        java.lang.String value)
Extends this ChangeEvent with the property named key with the value value. Note that if this event is to be rendered via the feed service, this extension will be rendered as a custom item element in the syndication feed, and so the value of key must be suitable for use as an XML element name (else it will be rejected).

NOTE: only (short) string exceptions are supported for a change event - other types supported by IExtensibleItem are NOT supported for change events.
